medical_history.history_of_present_illness: The patient experienced infertility over the previous 1.5 years; she was well but unable to conceive. She underwent evaluation for infertility at another healthcare facility during the year before this evaluation. A hysterosalpingogram performed 9 months prior indicated bilateral tubal occlusion.
medical_history.past_medical_history: No known significant past medical history; she has a history of completing two cycles of in vitro fertilization with high-quality embryo transfers but no successful implantation.
medical_history.family_history: Her father had hypertension, her maternal grandfather had colon cancer, and her maternal grandmother had diabetes mellitus; her mother and sibling were healthy.
medical_history.social_history: She drank alcohol infrequently, did not smoke or use illicit drugs. The patient had been married for 6 years, worked in an office, and had lived in multiple regions including Nepal, India, and the United States.
